window.bookSummaryJSON = "When Cora is savagely murdered with a hatchet, the extraordinary remark she made the previous day at her brother Richard's funeral suddenly takes on a chilling significance. <p>At the reading of Richard's will, Cora was clearly heard to say: \"It's been hushed up very nicely, hasn't it...But he was murdered, wasn't he?\"</p> <p>In desperation, the family solicitor turns to Hercule Poirot to unravel the mystery.</p>"; 
